This paper is about robotic manipulation and perception, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a method that uses visual models for object-centric perception, which suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) is also a likely sub-category. The method involves learning a policy, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning for learning manipulation tasks, which is a sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY).
